DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261117
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261118
SUMMARY:Deadline: Rauschenberg Medical Emergency Grants
DESCRIPTION:The Rauschenberg Medical Emergency Grants\, administered by the
  New York Foundation for the Arts on behalf of the Robert Rauschenberg Fou
 ndation\, provide one-time grants of up to USD 5\,000 to help artists in f
 inancial need cover recent unexpected medical\, dental\, and mental health
  emergencies. The program is open to generative visual and media artists a
 nd choreographers working in visual arts\, film\, video\, electronic and d
 igital arts\, and choreography who live anywhere in the United States\, th
 e District of Columbia\, a Tribal Nation\, or a U.S. Territory. Applicants
  must be artists in financial need\, with adjusted gross income at or belo
 w USD 80\,000 for an individual or USD 160\,000 for joint filers\, and mus
 t not have received a Rauschenberg Medical or Dancer Emergency Grant in th
 e past five years. Eligible expenses include emergency medical bills\, dia
 gnostics\, consultations\, therapy\, prescription medications\, emergency 
 dental care\, and transportation to appointments. The grant does not cover
  lost wages\, general living expenses\, or care for anyone other than the 
 artist. Applications are accepted during defined cycles\, with the current
  cycle running roughly from late October to mid November.\n\nOrganisation:
  New York Foundation for the Arts (NYFA) / Robert Rauschenberg Foundation\
 nLocation: United States (remote application)\nAward: One-time grants up t
 o USD 5\,000\nDuration: One-time grant\n\nMore: https://www.nyfa.org/award
 s-grants/rauschenberg-medical-emergency-grants/?utm_source=artificialnouve
 augrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
