UID:tech-workers-coalition-circuit-breakers-2026@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Circuit Breakers '26: Tech Worker Conference - Call for P
 roposals (New York City)
DESCRIPTION:Circuit Breakers '26 is a tech worker conference organised by v
 olunteers from across the tech labour movement\, bringing together workers
 \, organisers and activists in the tech industry to learn\, build communit
 y and strategise. Tech Workers Coalition defines tech workers broadly\, fr
 om software engineers and salespeople to warehouse workers and ride-share 
 drivers. The conference centres rank-and-file organising\, with workers sh
 aring stories\, running skills trainings and leading debates. The open cal
 l for proposals welcomes sessions on all aspects of labour organising in t
 ech\, with particular interest in three areas: Labor Organizing Against Im
 perialism\; Tech Workers Taking on Technology (layoffs\, surveillance\, wo
 rker control over AI and automation)\; and Bold Strategy (solidarity\, mem
 bership structures\, return-to-office actions\, cross-border organising). 
 Sessions can be proposed via a short form (about 10 minutes). New York Cit
 y\, 17-18 October 2026. This is not a grant and carries no funding\; it is
  a free call for conference talks. NOTE: the call-for-proposals deadline w
 as not yet published at time of listing\; confirm the submission deadline 
 and form link on the Circuit Breakers page.\n\nOrganisation: Tech Workers 
 Coalition\nLocation: New York City\, USA. In-person conference 17-18 Octob
 er 2026. Open to workers across the tech sector\, from software engineers 
 and salespeople to warehouse workers\, ride-share drivers and contractors.
 \nAward: No funding. This is a free call for talk/session proposals at a v
 olunteer-organised tech labour conference\, not a grant. No submission fee
 .\nDuration: Two-day conference\, 17-18 October 2026.\n\nMore: https://tec
 hworkerscoalition.org/circuit-breakers/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantd
 esk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://techworkerscoalition.org/circuit-breakers/?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:New York City\, USA. In-person conference 17-18 October 2026. Open
  to workers across the tech sector\, from software engineers and salespeop
 le to warehouse workers\, ride-share drivers and contractors.
END:VEVENT
