UID:pioneer-works-visual-arts-music-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260717
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260718
SUMMARY:Deadline: Pioneer Works: 2027 Open Call – Visual Arts and Music R
 esidency (Brooklyn\, NY)
DESCRIPTION:Pioneer Works in Red Hook\, Brooklyn invites applications from 
 emerging visual artists and musicians for its 2027 residency cohort. 12 Vi
 sual Arts residents (5-month residency) and 12 Music residents (1-month re
 sidency) are selected each year through a two-phase jury process. WHAT IS 
 PROVIDED: free studio space\; access to facilities including risograph pri
 nter\, darkroom\, ceramics studio\, large-format printer\, 3D printers\, t
 hermobinder\, and laser cutter\; biweekly studio visits with curators\, ga
 llerists\, critics\, and artists\; free access to all public programmes at
  Pioneer Works\, including Second Sundays (monthly open studios and perfor
 mances). FINANCIAL AWARD: USD 5\,000 for Visual Arts residents\; USD 3\,00
 0 for Music residents (each comprising a USD 2\,500 honorarium plus USD 50
 0/month for the residency duration)\; applicants' choice on how to spend i
 t. Pioneer Works does not provide housing\, travel\, or visa sponsorship. 
 ELIGIBILITY: open locally\, nationally\, and internationally\; collectives
  may apply (resources shared)\; current students and programme alumni are 
 not eligible. REVIEW PROCESS: phase one is internal scoring on technical a
 bility\, uniqueness of vision\, and future potential (nontraditional caree
 r paths given special consideration)\; highest scorers advance to an exter
 nal jury of art professionals and alumni who assess diversity of demograph
 ics and media\, genuine studio need\, and fit with Pioneer Works' public-f
 acing culture. Jury convenes September 2026\; all applicants notified by l
 ate September. Supported by Dalio Philanthropies\, the Andy Warhol Foundat
 ion\, NYC Department of Cultural Affairs\, New York State Council on the A
 rts\, and the National Endowment for the Arts. APPLY: via Pioneer Works we
 bsite by 17 July 2026 (extended). Questions: residency@pioneerworks.org.\n
 \nOrganisation: Pioneer Works\nLocation: Pioneer Works\, Red Hook\, Brookl
 yn\, New York\, USA\nAward: Visual Arts: USD 5\,000 one-time award (USD 2\
 ,500 honorarium + USD 500/month stipend for 5 months). Music: USD 3\,000 o
 ne-time award (USD 2\,500 honorarium + USD 500/month stipend for 1 month).
  Free studio space and facilities access. No housing or travel provided. N
 o application fee.\nDuration: Visual Arts: 5 months. Music: 1 month. Cohor
 t begins after jury decisions in late September 2026.\n\nMore: https://pio
 neerworks.org/residency?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=r
 eferral
URL:https://pioneerworks.org/residency?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdes
 k&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Pioneer Works\, Red Hook\, Brooklyn\, New York\, USA
END:VEVENT
