UID:jhu-agi-governance-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260730
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260731
SUMMARY:Deadline: AGI Governance Fellowship
DESCRIPTION:The AGI Governance Fellowship is the inaugural three-week inten
 sive run by Johns Hopkins University's School of Government and Policy (SO
 GP) to develop the next generation of leaders in AI governance. COVERS: fr
 ontier AI legislation at state and federal levels\; building societal resi
 lience amid rapid capability growth\; democratic practices in AGI alignmen
 t\; and designing new governing institutions for the AGI era. WHO SHOULD A
 PPLY: early-career researchers and practitioners (within roughly eight yea
 rs of undergrad) with solid foundations in AI governance\, including congr
 essional staffers\, AGI company employees\, recent CS or policy PhDs\, and
  nonprofit/civil society professionals\; a postgraduate degree or equivale
 nt experience is required. This is a capstone program for rising leaders\,
  not an intro course. FUNDING: travel\, accommodation\, and meals are full
 y covered. DATES: 8-25 September 2026 at the Hopkins Bloomberg Center in W
 ashington\, D.C. (in-person only). DEADLINE: apply by 15 July 2026 for ful
 l consideration\; rolling applications accepted. APPLY: https://sogp.jh.ed
 u/agi-governance-fellowship/\n\nOrganisation: Johns Hopkins University\, S
 chool of Government and Policy (SOGP)\nLocation: Hopkins Bloomberg Center\
 , Washington\, D.C. (in-person only)\nAward: Fully funded: travel\, accomm
 odation\, and meals covered.\nDuration: Three-week in-person intensive\, 8
 -25 September 2026\n\nMore: https://sogp.jh.edu/agi-governance-fellowship/
 ?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://sogp.jh.edu/agi-governance-fellowship/?utm_source=artificialnou
 veaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Hopkins Bloomberg Center\, Washington\, D.C. (in-person only)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ucross-general-residency-spring-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Ucross General Residency (All Disciplines): Spring 2027
DESCRIPTION:Ucross offers fully funded artist residencies on a working catt
 le ranch in the foothills of Wyoming's Bighorn Mountains\, providing unint
 errupted time and space free from the pressures and distractions of daily 
 life. Founded in 1981 with its first residency period in 1983\, Ucross hos
 ts approximately 115 individuals per year. Residencies range from two to s
 ix weeks\; at any one time up to ten people are in residence\, typically f
 our writers\, four visual artists\, and two composers. Each artist receive
 s living accommodations\, meals\, and work space at no charge. Lunches and
  dinners are prepared Monday to Friday by a professional chef (lunches del
 ivered to studios\, group dinners at 6 p.m.)\, with ample provisions for b
 reakfasts and weekends\; towels\, linens\, and weekly housekeeping are pro
 vided\, and there is cell service and wireless internet throughout. Reside
 nts provide their own working materials and arrange their own travel to Sh
 eridan\, Wyoming. The program is open to visual artists\, writers\, compos
 ers\, choreographers\, interdisciplinary artists\, performance artists\, a
 nd collaborative teams\; applicants must exhibit professional standing in 
 their field\, and both established and emerging artists are encouraged to 
 apply. Applications are submitted by discipline category: dance\, music/so
 und\, performance\, film/video\, playwriting/screenwriting\, visual art\, 
 fiction\, nonfiction\, poetry\, or interdisciplinary. The work sample and 
 project proposal are the most significant features of the application and 
 should correspond to one another\; if your work is in a single discipline\
 , select the category that best fits your project\, and apply under interd
 isciplinary only if the project genuinely combines multiple disciplines. W
 ork-sample requirements by category: DANCE\, 2-3 video files (each up to 8
  minutes and 200 MB\, or up to 3 Vimeo links\, with a timestamp if longer 
 than 8 minutes)\; MUSIC/SOUND\, 3-5 audio files (each up to 8 minutes and 
 200 MB\, or up to 3 Vimeo links\; musical scores welcome)\; PERFORMANCE an
 d FILM/VIDEO\, 1-3 video files (each up to 5 minutes and under 200 MB\, or
  up to 3 Vimeo/YouTube links\, with a timestamp if longer than 5 minutes)\
 ; PLAYWRITING/SCREENWRITING\, one complete play double-spaced noting the 2
 0-page section to read\; VISUAL ART\, 10 images at 4x6 inches and 300 dpi 
 (JPG or TIF\, no PDFs) plus a data sheet listing title\, medium\, size\, a
 nd year\; FICTION and NONFICTION\, 20 pages of double-spaced writing\; POE
 TRY\, 6-10 poems (10 maximum) in one PDF\, each poem starting on a new pag
 e\, total not exceeding 15 pages\; INTERDISCIPLINARY\, samples representin
 g the genres you plan to work in\, combining any of the above. All written
  work samples must be in English. There is a USD 40 application fee. The o
 pen call for the Spring 2027 session is open May 1 to July 15\, 2026 (appl
 y by 11:59 p.m. MT on July 15). Dedicated Fellowships for Native American 
 Visual Artists and Writers and a separate Culinary Residency are also offe
 red.\n\nOrganisation: Ucross Foundation\nLocation: Sheridan\, Wyoming\, US
 A\nAward: No charge for the residency\; living accommodations\, meals\, an
 d work space provided. USD 40 application fee.\nDuration: Spring session (
 February through early June 2027)\; residencies range from two to six week
 s\n\nMore: https://www.ucrossfoundation.org/residency-program.html?utm_sou
 rce=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.ucrossfoundation.org/residency-program.html?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Sheridan\, Wyoming\, USA
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ucross-fellowship-native-american-writers-spring-2027@artificialnouveau
 .github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Ucross Fellowship for Native American Writers: Spring 202
 7
DESCRIPTION:The Ucross Fellowship for Native American Writers is a dedicate
 d fellowship within Ucross Foundation's residency program\, offering fully
  funded time and space to write on a working cattle ranch in the foothills
  of Wyoming's Bighorn Mountains. The fellowship provides living accommodat
 ions\, meals\, and work space at no charge\, with no application fee. One 
 Fellowship winner is selected per session\; all applicants also have the o
 ption of being considered for a general Ucross residency. ELIGIBILITY: ope
 n to Native American writers who are practicing contemporary writers curre
 ntly producing work in one or more genres\, including but not limited to f
 iction\, nonfiction\, poetry\, drama\, screenwriting\, playwriting\, and h
 ybrid forms\; and who are enrolled members of a state-recognized or federa
 lly-recognized Tribe\, Pueblo\, Nation\, Native Community\, Political Enti
 ty\, or Alaskan Native Village. The work sample and project description ar
 e the most significant features of the application. Unless the work is gen
 uinely interdisciplinary (the genres interconnect)\, applicants are encour
 aged to apply in a single primary discipline and submit a work sample and 
 project description emphasizing that discipline. Work-sample requirements:
  FICTION\, 20 pages of double-spaced fiction (a novel excerpt\, a story\, 
 several stories\, or a combination)\; NONFICTION\, 20 pages of double-spac
 ed nonfiction\; POETRY\, 10 pages of poetry (may be single-spaced)\; PLAYW
 RITING\, one complete play (production documentation may be included if re
 levant)\, noting the 20 pages for reviewers to read\; SCREENWRITING\, one 
 complete screenplay (production documentation may be included if relevant)
 \, noting the 20 pages for reviewers to read. All writing samples should i
 nclude your full name. The open call for the Spring 2027 session closes Ju
 ly 15\, 2026 (apply by 11:59 p.m. MT). A separate Ucross Fellowship for Na
 tive American Visual Artists is also offered.\n\nOrganisation: Ucross Foun
 dation\nLocation: Sheridan\, Wyoming\, USA\nAward: Fully funded fellowship
  residency\; living accommodations\, meals\, and work space provided. No a
 pplication fee.\nDuration: Spring session (February through early June 202
 7)\; residencies range from two to six weeks\n\nMore: https://www.ucrossfo
 undation.org/residency-program.html?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&
 utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.ucrossfoundation.org/residency-program.html?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Sheridan\, Wyoming\, USA
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
