SUMMARY:Deadline: Google Data Center Community AI Fellowship
DESCRIPTION:The Google Data Center Community AI Fellowship is a fully funde
 d fellowship for community leaders and entrepreneurs using AI or technolog
 y to create local impact in Google Data Center communities. Fellows receiv
 e AI training\, mentorship\, access to Google resources\, and a USD 1\,000
  community development stipend to support projects that deliver local impa
 ct. WHO IT'S FOR: community leaders and entrepreneurs applying AI or techn
 ology to community-level challenges in Google Data Center communities. WHA
 T'S OFFERED: AI training\, mentorship\, Google resources\, and a USD 1\,00
 0 stipend. PRIORITY DEADLINE: 12 July 2026. TO APPLY: submit the applicati
 on via the Watson Institute program page.\n\nOrganisation: Google (with Wa
 tson Institute)\nLocation: Google Data Center communities\, United States.
  Fellowship delivered with mentorship and training.\nAward: Fully funded f
 ellowship including AI training\, mentorship\, Google resources\, and a US
 D 1\,000 community development stipend. No application fee.\nDuration: Fel
 lowship program with AI training and mentorship (dates per program).\n\nMo
 re: https://watson.is/google-data-center-community-ai-fellowship-applicati
 on/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
