UID:gallery-penn-college-exhibitions-2027-28@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: The Gallery at Penn College: 2027-28 Call for Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:The Gallery at Penn College (Pennsylvania College of Technology
 \, Williamsport\, PA) invites artists to apply for solo\, two-person\, or 
 group exhibitions for its 2027-28 season. All entries are juried through a
  blind selection process by a gallery committee of faculty\, staff\, K-12 
 art educators\, and community artists\; review takes place during the Fall
  semester and artists receive notification in January. PROVIDED: housing\,
  meals\, a solo exhibition honorarium\, and a shipping and travel stipend.
  Promotional support includes an annual gallery catalog\, postcards\, pres
 s releases\, and web and social media. THE SPACE: the Gallery is 3\,000 sq
 uare feet with 82-250 running feet of linear wall space and an 11'4" ceili
 ng. All exhibitions are installed by Gallery staff\; site-specific install
 ations requiring artist installation need a planning document approved bef
 ore scheduling. Artists must have enough work for a solo exhibition unless
  applying for a two-person show. ENGAGEMENT: campus visits are an importan
 t part of programming (some exhibitions are scheduled without a visit). Pe
 nn College offers a B.S. in Graphic Design with foundation courses in draw
 ing\, 2D and 3D design\, visual literacy\, painting\, ceramics\, wood scul
 pture\, printmaking\, and computer graphics\; artists are encouraged to pr
 opose class-specific programs and optional community workshops. Visiting a
 rtists give a 20-30 minute gallery talk during the public reception (held 
 Tuesdays through Thursdays). TO APPLY: 10-15 digital images of work (JPG/J
 PEG only\, max 4 MB each)\, an image list with dimensions and medium\, a C
 V\, and an artist statement. For two-person or group proposals\, provide d
 etails in the comments\; for video work\, upload a PDF with video links an
 d details. Deadline 31 August 2026 for the 2027-28 season.\n\nOrganisation
 : The Gallery at Penn College (Pennsylvania College of Technology)\nLocati
 on: Williamsport\, Pennsylvania\, United States (campus of Pennsylvania Co
 llege of Technology). Williamsport Regional Airport connects to Washington
 -Dulles\; no other direct flights or trains.\nAward: Housing\, meals\, a s
 olo exhibition honorarium\, and a shipping and travel stipend are provided
 . No application fee.\nDuration: Exhibitions scheduled during the 2027-28 
 season. Jurying takes place in the Fall 2026 semester\; artists are notifi
 ed in January 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.pct.edu/gallery/exhibitions-entry
 -form?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.pct.edu/gallery/exhibitions-entry-form?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Williamsport\, Pennsylvania\, United States (campus of Pennsylvani
 a College of Technology). Williamsport Regional Airport connects to Washin
 gton-Dulles\; no other direct flights or trains.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:railyard-art-project-santa-fe-2026-27@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260805
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260806
SUMMARY:Deadline: Railyard Art Project: Call for Temporary Public Art (Sant
 a Fe)
DESCRIPTION:The Railyard Art Project (RAP) facilitates temporary public art
  installations by established and emerging artists and arts collectives in
  Santa Fe's Railyard Park + Plaza. RAP is accepting proposals for temporar
 y public art installations and creative projects\; thanks to funding from 
 Santa Fe's Arts and Culture Commission\, two projects will be hosted betwe
 en October 2026 and June 2027\, each receiving a USD 3\,500 honorarium plu
 s marketing support and liability insurance. THEMES: the RAP Committee enc
 ourages collaboration across disciplines (art\, science\, history) and wel
 comes thoughtful\, challenging\, playful\, and edifying art in the context
  of social and cultural expression and environmental sustainability. Propo
 sed projects must physically withstand outdoor public display and engage t
 he community by responding to the natural and social landscape of the park
 . SELECTION CRITERIA: overall artistic merit\; context and familiarity wit
 h the proposed site\; practical viability\; and potential for community en
 gagement and cultural/educational enrichment. Artists should select an eli
 gible area of the park's open space and describe the project in detail\; p
 hotos or renderings may be uploaded with the application (a map of Railyar
 d Art Locations is linked from the program page). The RAP Committee\, made
  up of community members and Park + Plaza stakeholders\, selects and sched
 ules the exhibitions\; a formal in-person presentation may be requested de
 pending on complexity. CONDITIONS: the park operates under a Conservation 
 Easement\, so installations cannot be located on planted areas\, no stakin
 g of any kind is permitted (including during install/de-install)\, and not
 hing may be hung from trees. Artists lend artwork at their own risk (no pr
 otection against vandalism or weather damage\, and artists are responsible
  for repairs). Installs and de-installs must be coordinated in advance wit
 h the RAP Committee or Railyard Park Conservancy staff\, with a Committee 
 or staff member on site throughout. Application deadline 5 August 2026.\n\
 nOrganisation: Railyard Art Project (Railyard Park + Plaza)\nLocation: San
 ta Fe\, New Mexico\, United States (Railyard Park + Plaza\, City-owned pro
 perty under a Conservation Easement).\nAward: USD 3\,500 honorarium per pr
 oject (two projects selected)\, plus marketing support and liability insur
 ance. Funded by Santa Fe's Arts and Culture Commission. No application fee
 .\nDuration: Two projects hosted between October 2026 and June 2027.\n\nMo
 re: https://railyardpark.org/public-art-program/?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://railyardpark.org/public-art-program/?utm_source=artificialnouve
 augrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Santa Fe\, New Mexico\, United States (Railyard Park + Plaza\, Cit
 y-owned property under a Conservation Easement).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:target-margin-tmt-institute-fellowship-2026-27@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260722
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260723
SUMMARY:Deadline: Target Margin Theater: TMT Institute Fellowship 2026-27
DESCRIPTION:Target Margin Theater invites applications for its next cohort 
 of TMT Institute Fellows for the 2026/2027 season. The Institute is a coho
 rt of artists who seek to radically disrupt and re-examine their existing 
 practice without any goal or expected result: pure experimentation with no
  product-oriented end goal. Fellows pursue no project\, no developmental s
 tage\, no deliverable\; misfires\, dead ends\, and bad ideas are considere
 d a fruitful part of the work. SUPPORT: TMT provides space\, material reso
 urces\, collaborators\, and a USD 2\,000 stipend. STRUCTURE: three short i
 ntensive sessions at Target Margin Theater in Brooklyn (5-8 November 2026\
 , 8-10 January 2027\, and 19-21 March 2027\, all day with some evening hou
 rs)\, monthly breakfasts at Junior's in Brooklyn (20 October\, 30 November
 \, 4 January\, 1 February\, 8 March\, 5 April\, 3 May)\, and occasional ex
 cursions. After the second intensive\, each Fellow commits to an explorati
 on pursued outside group gatherings\, supported by TMT resources. The seas
 on ends with an Open Studio weekend in June 2027 to share explorations wit
 h the community\; this is not a performance and should not be an audience-
 attended\, time-bounded show. WHO CAN APPLY: artists from any discipline w
 ithin or outside theater\, as well as production\, technical\, and adminis
 trative workers in the arts. Applicants must have an established\, existin
 g body of work and practice they are committed to changing\; do not apply 
 with a project. Recent graduates of training programs are unlikely to be a
 ppropriate candidates\; no formal education level or degree is required. S
 ELECTION: TMT staff and artistic community review applications and invite 
 a handful of candidates to interview\; all applicants are notified by Octo
 ber. Deadline: Wednesday 22 July 2026\, 11:59 pm EST.\n\nOrganisation: Tar
 get Margin Theater\nLocation: Brooklyn\, New York\, United States (Sunset 
 Park). Fellows must be available in person for intensives\, monthly breakf
 asts\, and excursions.\nAward: USD 2\,000 stipend\, plus space\, material 
 resources\, and collaborators to support each Fellow's experiments. No app
 lication fee.\nDuration: 2026-27 season: three intensive sessions in Brook
 lyn (5-8 November 2026\, 8-10 January 2027\, 19-21 March 2027)\, monthly b
 reakfasts October 2026 through May 2027\, and an Open Studio weekend in Ju
 ne 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.targetmargin.org/institute/?utm_source=artif
 icialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.targetmargin.org/institute/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Brooklyn\, New York\, United States (Sunset Park). Fellows must be
  available in person for intensives\, monthly breakfasts\, and excursions.
END:VEVENT
