UID:woodward-newman-award-2027-28@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: Woodward/Newman Award 2027-28 (Constellation Stage & Scre
 en)
DESCRIPTION:The Woodward/Newman Award\, started with the support of Joanne 
 Woodward\, Newman's Own Foundation and the Newman family\, is awarded annu
 ally by Constellation Stage & Screen to the best unpublished new play. The
  winner receives a USD 3\,000 cash prize (in lieu of royalties) and a full
  production in the Mainstage season\, with housing and transportation prov
 ided. The contest format and submission fees have been eliminated: submiss
 ions are reviewed on an ongoing basis and are also considered for all seve
 n production slots in the season\, including TYA (theatre for young audien
 ces) shows. Full-length plays should run 75 to 135 minutes\; TYA shows ove
 r 40 minutes. Plays must be unpublished at submission (independently publi
 shed is acceptable)\; limit of two submissions per playwright per year\; m
 usicals may include demos. Plays submitted by midnight 31 August 2026 are 
 considered for the 2027-28 season\; later submissions roll to 2028-29. All
  submissions are kept on file for two years.\n\nOrganisation: Constellatio
 n Stage & Screen\nLocation: Bloomington\, Indiana\, USA. Open submissions 
 of unpublished plays\; production takes place in Bloomington.\nAward: USD 
 3\,000 cash prize (in lieu of royalties) plus a full production in Constel
 lation's Mainstage season\; housing and transportation provided. No submis
 sion fee.\nDuration: Winner announced by 15 May 2027\; production in the 2
 027-28 season. Submissions stay on file and under consideration for two ye
 ars.\n\nMore: https://seeconstellation.org/get-involved/submit-play/?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://seeconstellation.org/get-involved/submit-play/?utm_source=artif
 icialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Bloomington\, Indiana\, USA. Open submissions of unpublished plays
 \; production takes place in Bloomington.
END:VEVENT
