SUMMARY:Deadline: Cafe Royal Cultural Foundation: Performance Grant (Summer
  2026)
DESCRIPTION:The Cafe Royal Cultural Foundation NYC Performance Grant suppor
 ts individual artists producing theatre\, dance and performance art (which
  may be accompanied by music) moving toward a public performance. The Summ
 er 2026 cycle offers up to $10\,000 for eligible production costs: actors\
 , dancers and guest performers\, director/choreographer/composer and creat
 ive-team fees\, costumes\, lighting\, sound\, scenic\, props and set\, reh
 earsal and venue rental\, and production and technical staff. Funds do not
  cover the creation or composition of new work\; if the performance is a p
 lay it must be a full production (readings do not qualify). ELIGIBILITY: i
 ndividual performers only (not groups or organizations) who are US citizen
 s or resident aliens\, current NYC residents who have lived in the city at
  least one year and will remain through project completion. This cycle acc
 epts only 40 applications and closes early if that cap is reached. Applica
 nts may submit up to 5 video links. Apply via the foundation's performance
  page. Deadline: 3 August 2026\, 9:00 am ET (or earlier if 40 applications
  are received).\n\nOrganisation: Cafe Royal Cultural Foundation NYC\nLocat
 ion: New York City (five boroughs)\, or a location in close proximity to N
 YC approved by the foundation\, USA\nAward: Up to $10\,000 for production 
 costs (performers\, collaborators\, rehearsal and venue rental\, design el
 ements\, technical staff\, etc.). Does not fund the creation or compositio
 n of new work. No application fee.\nDuration: Production grant\; performan
 ce must start no sooner than 1 November 2026 and complete by 22 September 
 2027\n\nMore: https://caferoyalculturalfoundation.org/performance-page?utm
 _source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
